Privacy Policy

Effective Date: January 14, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how OptimaAI (“we”, “our”, or “us”) collects, uses, and protects user information when interacting with our WhatsApp Business account.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following information when users interact with our WhatsApp Business account:
- WhatsApp phone number
- Messages sent to our WhatsApp Business account
- Message timestamps and metadata

2. How We Use Information
We use the collected information solely to:
- Respond to user inquiries
- Provide automated and human-assisted customer support
- Improve our messaging services

3. Data Storage
We do not permanently store personal user data. Message data may be temporarily processed for the purpose of generating automated responses.

4. Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or share personal data with third parties, except where required by law or to operate the WhatsApp Business Cloud service provided by Meta Platforms, Inc.

5. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect user data from unauthorized access, misuse, or disclosure.

6. User Rights
Users may request access to or deletion of their personal data at any time by contacting us using the email provided below.

7. Third-Party Services
This service operates using WhatsApp Business Cloud APIs and related services provided by Meta Platforms, Inc., which are governed by Meta’s own privacy policies.

8. Contact Information
For privacy-related questions or requests, contact:

Email: w.mugwe@yahoo.com

By using our WhatsApp Business account, you consent to this Privacy Policy.
